<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.65.34" />

<fw type="curatorial">34</fw>

<opener>
<dateline>
5835 Vine Street<lb/>
Lincoln, Nebraska 68505<lb/>
May 30, 1973
</dateline>

<address>
<addrLine>Dr. Leo E. Oliva</addrLine>
<addrLine>Department of History</addrLine>
<addrLine>Fort Hays Kansas State College</addrLine>
<addrLine>Hays, Kansas 61601</addrLine>
</address>

<salute>Dear Dr. Oliva:</salute>
</opener>
<p>Many thanks for your kind letter of May 21, 1973, and for the autographed copy of your book, <hi rend="underline">Soldiers on the Santa Fe Trail</hi>. I am looking forward to having the book read to me as my eyes are not as good as they should be. I am sure I will find the book fascinating.</p>

<p>Just at present, as for some months past, I am occupied with recording my work for the United Artists. They are planning a series of twelve albums, the first of which will be out in August.</p>

<p>Please know that I am deeply grateful to you for your thought of me. How I do wish I could plunge in head first and read the whole book at a sitting. I am especially interested in the Santa Fe Trail, and I am sure you are going to give me a great deal of pleasure.</p>
<closer>
<salute>Kindest thoughts,</salute>



<signed>John G. Neihardt</signed>


<note>JGN:nh</note>
</closer>

</div1>
